00:00:25.270 --> 00:00:32.040
rHealth is a universal health sensor that
allows people to diagnose themselves anywhere.

00:00:32.040 --> 00:00:36.570
Using a single drop of blood the device can
test for hundreds of lab values including

00:00:36.570 --> 00:00:42.670
vitamin D, calcium and red or white blood
cells by using nanoscale test strips read

00:00:42.670 --> 00:00:43.930
by laser.

00:00:43.930 --> 00:00:48.410
NASA helped fund its development to better
monitor the health of astronauts and it uses

00:00:48.410 --> 00:00:53.530
1500x less blood than conventional lab tests.

00:00:53.530 --> 00:00:58.210
It recently won the grand prize from Xprize
and they say it can help diagnose diseases

00:00:58.210 --> 00:01:01.220
before you have them including cancer.

00:01:01.220 --> 00:01:06.149
Rescue operations could get a huge boost from
cyborg cockroaches.

00:01:06.149 --> 00:01:10.759
Researchers at North Carolina State University
are attaching circuit boards and unidirectional

00:01:10.759 --> 00:01:16.569
microphones to the insects so they'll be compelled
to move towards the sounds of a person struggling

00:01:16.569 --> 00:01:18.240
or crying for help.

00:01:18.240 --> 00:01:23.270
An army of these biobots would be released
to help first responders gather information

00:01:23.270 --> 00:01:25.909
in areas they can’t initially enter.

00:01:25.909 --> 00:01:29.880
And cockroaches are ideal candidates because
they’re small, hard to kill, and do not

00:01:29.880 --> 00:01:32.570
likely experience feelings of pain.

00:01:32.570 --> 00:01:37.100
The food and fuel of the future could be grown
on highway algae farms.

00:01:37.100 --> 00:01:43.049
An experimental garden in Switzerland on a
viaduct over a small highway uses the unobstructed

00:01:43.049 --> 00:01:48.060
sunlight and overabundance of Co2 from vehicles
to grow algae.

00:01:48.060 --> 00:01:53.149
Built this summer it proves how highways could
be easily modified to grow food, biofuel,

00:01:53.149 --> 00:01:54.939
and clean the air.

