Retroreflective projection technology could
make cars see through.

00:02:06.780 --> 00:02:11.300
Developed at Keio University in Japan it uses
mirrors, cameras, and fabric lined with tiny

00:02:11.300 --> 00:02:15.569
glass beads to project outside images inside
the car.

00:02:15.569 --> 00:02:20.061
Aside from eliminating blind spots in your
car, it could be used to let pilots see the

00:02:20.061 --> 00:02:25.660
runway beneath them, create gloves that allow
surgeons to see through their hands, and put

00:02:25.660 --> 00:02:28.849
us one step closer to invisibility cloaks.

00:02:28.849 --> 00:02:32.810
The Altaeros BAT is a wind turbine that floats
in the sky.

00:02:32.810 --> 00:02:37.470
The helium-filled device is designed to reach
altitudes of 1,000 feet, where air currents

00:02:37.470 --> 00:02:40.319
are 5-8 times more powerful.

00:02:40.319 --> 00:02:44.412
Set to debut in Alaska for an 18 month testing
period, the BAT (Buoyant Airborne Turbine),

00:02:44.412 --> 00:02:48.989
will bring power to families living off of
the grid while also providing WiFi and cell

00:02:48.989 --> 00:02:50.140
phone service.

